                            <comment id="13210278" author="kristwaa" created="Fri, 17 Feb 2012 14:05:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching patch 1a, which replaces a set of characters from the string returned by TestCase.getName().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suspect the list isn&apos;t exhaustive, but it may already include characters that are allowed in some file system. The point here is just to make sure the directory creation works. In my case it failed due to putting &apos;&amp;lt;&amp;gt;&apos; in a test name (compatibility test).&lt;br/&gt;
More characters that should go in?&lt;br/&gt;
Is there perhaps a method in the Java-API that will remove illegal chars?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch ready for review.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13210283" author="kristwaa" created="Fri, 17 Feb 2012 14:09:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It could be argued that the way to solve this is to do nothing, let runBare fail when/if the test fails, and then change the test name. The reason why I consider another solutions is that using &quot;special characters&quot; in the test name may be nice when dynamically generating test cases.&lt;br/&gt;
As an example, I was using &quot;client 10.1.3.1 &amp;lt;&amp;gt; server 10.8.2.2&quot; as the name of the test case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13210397" author="dagw" created="Fri, 17 Feb 2012 17:34:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for fixing this! Why not just replace all non-identifier characters with underscore or dash? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13211694" author="kristwaa" created="Mon, 20 Feb 2012 06:45:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Dag.&lt;br/&gt;
Something along the lines of patch 2a?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BTW, this code must be CDC/J2ME compatible.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13212278" author="dagw" created="Tue, 21 Feb 2012 01:22:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good to me. +1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13212461" author="kristwaa" created="Tue, 21 Feb 2012 08:39:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Dag &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Committed patch 2a to trunk with revision 1291657.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
